{
  "stem": "15768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went away on a vacation together with my aunt and uncle and the cousins and had really a comfortable and comfortable and, I would say, very happy kind of a existence.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I-- I couldn't think of anything that I would have done different in my youth.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a wonderful foundation, having the influence of all these loving relatives and that I was extremely attached to.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "High holidays, we were always at my grandmother's house.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] it was-- it was always both a religious experience and a fun experience because we children always did a certain amount of cutting up.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, he, [SIGHS] not only that he shepherded me through-- through my tomboy years and patched me up [LAUGHS] whenever I got myself into trouble.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he was also a-- a mentor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he had put one of my cousins through medical school, and it was sort of a foregone conclusion that he was also going to put me through medical school.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the days of horse and buggies, I used to go on rounds with him to see patients in the countryside.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Later on, he had a car.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was always a [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] informative experience how he related to people and how-- how the people in the town really respected him a great deal.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when I was at my grandmother's, I usually went downstairs and moseyed around his office.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he told me about the sterilizer and all the different things that he uses when he sees patients and so forth.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So there was a very close bond.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- he-- he had to check me for broken bones when I jumped out of unexpected places.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
